The paper deals with clock synchronization in sensor networks, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and networked systems (cs.NI). The algorithm proposed in the paper also has the gradient property, which is a concept related to optimization and control theory (cs.SY). The paper also mentions an upper bound on the network's diameter, which is a characteristic of distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the rate at which logical clocks progress in time, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT).
